CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1941, pg. 16, reads: "Fight Fanatics Gab With Winner - Teddy Horne, left, and Woogie Harris, right, two of Pittsburgh's most rabid fight fans are pictured here congratulating George Burnette, Detroit middleweight, who defeated Mose Brown at The Gardens Monday night in a prefight. Horne and Harris seldom miss an important fight, whether it is in Pittsburgh or elsewhere.  Burnette won by a technical knockout when Brown was forced stop due to an eye injury. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Teddy Horne and boxer George Burnette shaking hands with William "Woogie" Harris, in Crawford Grill No. 1
